<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="228" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="228">Distribution, phenology and biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="228">
Known only from Nigeria. While no precise location is recorded the words 'Soedan 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Savanne’">Savanne'</normalizedToken>
suggest a north-easterly location, perhaps near Lake Chad (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="228">c.</emphasis>
<geoCoordinate degrees="11" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="55555" value="11.0">11°N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="12" direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="55555" value="12.0">12°E</geoCoordinate>
- 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 26. Distribution of Astochia species: A. lumarius sp. nov., A. silva sp. nov., similis sp. nov., A. sodalis, A. strachani." figureDoi="10.3897/AfrInvertebr.60.38432.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/346350" pageId="13" pageNumber="228" tableDoi="10.3897/AfrInvertebr.60.38432.figure26">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
), where the environment could be described as savanna. Collected in February (Table 
<tableCitation captionStartId="T1" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/77ABE6B430CB8ADF8FCB922543B38124" pageId="13" pageNumber="228" tableUuid="77ABE6B430CB8ADF8FCB922543B38124">1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
